  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q07', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Which case held that balance between Fundamental Rights and DPSP is part of the basic structure?', 'Maneka Gandhi case (1978)', 'Minerva Mills case (1980)', 'Golaknath case (1967)', 'Gopalan case (1950)', 'B', 'In Minerva Mills (1980), the Supreme Court held the balance between FRs and DPSP is part of the basic structure.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties-q08', 'upsc-polity-dpsp-and-fundamental-duties', 'Article 39A, providing for free legal aid and equal justice, was added by which amendment?', '42nd Amendment', '44th Amendment', '86th Amendment', '1st Amendment', 'A', 'Article 39A on equal justice and free legal aid was inserted by the 42nd Amendment of 1976.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q01', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Under which Article is the Supreme Court of India established?', 'Article 32', 'Article 124', 'Article 137', 'Article 143', 'B', 'Article 124 establishes the Supreme Court of India and provides for its composition.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q02', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'What is the present sanctioned strength of judges in the Supreme Court (including the CJI)?', '31', '26', '30', '34', 'D', 'The sanctioned strength is 34: the Chief Justice of India plus up to 33 other judges.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q03', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Consider the following statements:
1. A Supreme Court judge holds office until 65 years of age.
2. Article 137 empowers the court to review its own judgments.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'SC judges retire at 65; Article 137 grants the power to review the court''s own judgments.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q04', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The advisory jurisdiction of the Supreme Court is provided under which Article?', 'Article 131', 'Article 132', 'Article 136', 'Article 143', 'D', 'Article 143 allows the President to seek the advisory opinion of the Supreme Court.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q05', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The 99th Amendment that created the NJAC was struck down by the Supreme Court in which year?', '2010', '2013', '2018', '2015', 'D', 'The Supreme Court struck down the NJAC (99th Amendment) in 2015, restoring the collegium system.', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q06', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Consider the following statements about writ jurisdiction:
1. A High Court issues writs under Article 226.
2. Article 226 is wider than Article 32 as it covers legal rights too.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'High Courts issue writs under Article 226, which is wider than Article 32 since it covers legal rights too.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q07', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'Public Interest Litigation (PIL) in India was pioneered chiefly by which judges?', 'H.J. Kania and M. Patanjali Sastri', 'M. Hidayatullah and S.M. Sikri', 'A.N. Ray and Y.V. Chandrachud', 'P.N. Bhagwati and V.R. Krishna Iyer', 'D', 'Justices P.N. Bhagwati and V.R. Krishna Iyer pioneered PIL by relaxing the rule of locus standi.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review-q08', 'upsc-polity-judiciary-and-judicial-review', 'The collegium system for the appointment of judges evolved from which cases?', 'The First and Second Judges Cases', 'The Second and Third Judges Cases', 'The Kesavananda and Minerva cases', 'The Golaknath and Maneka Gandhi cases', 'B', 'The collegium system evolved primarily from the Second (1993) and Third (1998) Judges Cases.', 7),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q01', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Which one of the following is a constitutional body?', 'NITI Aayog', 'National Human Rights Commission', 'Election Commission of India', 'Central Information Commission', 'C', 'The Election Commission is a constitutional body under Article 324; the others are non-constitutional or statutory.', 0),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q02', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Comptroller and Auditor General of India is provided for under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 148', 'Article 315', 'Article 324', 'B', 'Article 148 provides for the CAG, the guardian of the public purse who audits government accounts.', 1),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q03', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Finance Commission is constituted under Article 280.
2. It is set up every five years to recommend tax devolution.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Finance Commission, under Article 280, is constituted every five years for Centre-State tax devolution.', 2),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q04', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) was established under which law?', 'Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993', 'Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013', 'RTI Act, 2005', 'Right to Education Act, 2009', 'A', 'The NHRC is a statutory body set up under the Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993.', 3),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q05', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The National Commission for Backward Classes became a constitutional body under which Article?', 'Article 280', 'Article 338', 'Article 338B', 'Article 324', 'C', 'The NCBC gained constitutional status under Article 338B via the 102nd Amendment (2018).', 4),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q06', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The UPSC is a constitutional body under Article 315.
2. The Lokpal is a statutory body created in 2013.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The UPSC is constitutional under Article 315; the Lokpal is statutory under the 2013 Act.', 5),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q07', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Central Information Commission functions under which Act?', 'Protection of Human Rights Act, 1993', 'Right to Information Act, 2005', 'Companies Act, 2013', 'Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013', 'B', 'The CIC is a statutory body that functions under the Right to Information Act, 2005.', 6),
  ('upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies-q08', 'upsc-polity-constitutional-and-statutory-bodies', 'The Attorney General of India is provided for under which Article?', 'Article 315', 'Article 148', 'Article 280', 'Article 76', 'D', 'Article 76 provides for the Attorney General, the highest law officer of the Union.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Who was the first president of the Indian National Congress?', 'A.O. Hume', 'Dadabhai Naoroji', 'W.C. Bonnerjee', 'Surendranath Banerjee', 'C', 'W.C. Bonnerjee presided over the first Congress session in 1885; A.O. Hume founded the party.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The ''Drain Theory'' explaining the economic exploitation of India was propounded by:', 'Gopal Krishna Gokhale', 'Dadabhai Naoroji', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak', 'Bipin Chandra Pal', 'B', 'Dadabhai Naoroji propounded the Drain Theory in his work Poverty and Un-British Rule in India.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Congress split into Moderates and Extremists at the Surat session of 1907.
2. They reunited at the Lucknow session of 1916.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Surat Split occurred in 1907 and the two factions reunited at Lucknow in 1916.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Which trio is collectively known as ''Lal-Bal-Pal''?', 'Lajpat Rai, Tilak, Bipin Chandra Pal', 'Lajpat Rai, Bonnerjee, Pherozeshah Mehta', 'Lala Hardayal, Tilak, B.G. Pal', 'Lajpat Rai, Gokhale, Naoroji', 'A', 'Lal-Bal-Pal were the extremist leaders Lala Lajpat Rai, Bal Gangadhar Tilak and Bipin Chandra Pal.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The slogan ''Swaraj is my birthright and I shall have it'' was given by:', 'Lala Lajpat Rai', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak', 'Bipin Chandra Pal', 'Aurobindo Ghosh', 'B', 'Bal Gangadhar Tilak gave the famous slogan asserting Swaraj as a birthright.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Moderates relied on petitions, prayers and protests.
2. The Swadeshi Movement was triggered by the Partition of Bengal in 1905.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Moderates used the 3 Ps; the 1905 Partition of Bengal triggered the Swadeshi Movement.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The Indian National Congress was founded in which year?', '1857', '1905', '1916', '1885', 'D', 'The Indian National Congress was founded in 1885 by A.O. Hume.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-moderates-and-extremists', 'The Lucknow session of 1916 is notable because:', 'It marked the founding of the Congress', 'It launched the Quit India Movement', 'It saw the Lucknow Pact with the Muslim League', 'It abolished the Drain Theory', 'C', 'The 1916 Lucknow session reunited Congress factions and produced the Lucknow Pact with the Muslim League.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Gandhi''s first Satyagraha in India, in 1917, was launched at:', 'Kheda', 'Champaran', 'Ahmedabad', 'Dandi', 'B', 'The Champaran Satyagraha of 1917 opposed the tinkathia system imposed on indigo cultivators in Bihar.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The Non-Cooperation Movement was withdrawn following which incident?', 'Jallianwala Bagh massacre', 'Partition of Bengal', 'Failure of the Cripps Mission', 'Chauri Chaura incident', 'D', 'Gandhi withdrew the Non-Cooperation Movement in 1922 after the violent Chauri Chaura incident.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Dandi March began on 12 March 1930.
2. The Civil Disobedience Movement broke the salt law.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Dandi March started on 12 March 1930 and launched Civil Disobedience by breaking the salt law.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The slogan ''Do or Die'' is associated with which movement?', 'Non-Cooperation Movement', 'Quit India Movement', 'Swadeshi Movement', 'Civil Disobedience Movement', 'B', 'Gandhi gave the ''Do or Die'' call during the Quit India Movement of 1942.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'The Kheda Satyagraha of 1918 was launched for:', 'Repeal of the salt tax', 'Abolition of the tinkathia system', 'Higher wages for mill workers', 'Remission of land revenue during crop failure', 'D', 'The Kheda Satyagraha in Gujarat demanded remission of land revenue after crop failure.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Quit India Movement was triggered by the failure of the Cripps Mission.
2. The Gandhi-Irwin Pact led to Congress joining the Second Round Table Conference.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Quit India followed the Cripps Mission failure; the 1931 Gandhi-Irwin Pact preceded the Second Round Table Conference.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'In which year did Mahatma Gandhi return to India from South Africa?', '1909', '1915', '1920', '1919', 'B', 'Gandhi returned to India in 1915 and transformed the freedom struggle into a mass movement.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-gandhian-mass-movements', 'Gandhi''s first hunger strike in India was undertaken during which event?', 'Champaran Satyagraha', 'Kheda Satyagraha', 'Ahmedabad Mill Strike', 'Dandi March', 'C', 'Gandhi undertook his first hunger strike during the 1918 Ahmedabad Mill Strike.', 7),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q01', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Brahmo Samaj was founded in 1828 by:', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar', 'A', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy founded the Brahmo Samaj in 1828 and is called the Father of Indian Renaissance.', 0),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q02', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The slogan ''Back to the Vedas'' was given by:', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Jyotiba Phule', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'B', 'Dayananda Saraswati, founder of the Arya Samaj (1875), gave the slogan ''Back to the Vedas''.', 1),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q03', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Sati was abolished by Lord William Bentinck in 1829.
2. Raja Ram Mohan Roy campaigned against Sati.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Lord William Bentinck abolished Sati in 1829, supported by Raja Ram Mohan Roy''s campaign.', 2),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q04', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Satyashodhak Samaj (1873) was founded by:', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Colonel Olcott', 'Dayananda Saraswati', 'Jyotiba Phule', 'D', 'Jyotiba Phule founded the Satyashodhak Samaj in 1873 to fight caste oppression.', 3),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q05', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Who championed the cause of widow remarriage, leading to the Act of 1856?', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'Madame Blavatsky', 'Swami Vivekananda', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar', 'D', 'Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar championed widow remarriage, which led to the Widow Remarriage Act of 1856.', 4),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q06', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Ramakrishna Mission was founded by Swami Vivekananda in 1897.
2. The Aligarh Movement was led by Sir Syed Ahmed Khan.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Vivekananda founded the Ramakrishna Mission in 1897; Sir Syed Ahmed Khan led the Aligarh Movement.', 5),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q07', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Shuddhi movement, aimed at reconversion, was started by which organisation?', 'Arya Samaj', 'Brahmo Samaj', 'Ramakrishna Mission', 'Theosophical Society', 'A', 'The Arya Samaj, founded by Dayananda Saraswati, started the Shuddhi reconversion movement.', 6),
  ('upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements-q08', 'upsc-modern-history-socio-religious-reform-movements', 'The Theosophical Society was founded in 1875 by:', 'Annie Besant alone', 'Sir Syed Ahmed Khan', 'Raja Ram Mohan Roy', 'Madame Blavatsky and Colonel Olcott', 'D', 'The Theosophical Society was founded in 1875 by Madame Blavatsky and Colonel Olcott.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Mohenjo-daro is situated on the banks of which river?', 'Indus', 'Ravi', 'Ghaggar', 'Sutlej', 'A', 'Mohenjo-daro, meaning Mound of the Dead, is located on the Indus river and housed the Great Bath.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The site of Lothal is best known for its:', 'Artificial dockyard', 'Citadel', 'Great Bath', 'Pillared hall', 'A', 'Lothal in Gujarat had an artificial dockyard, evidence of Harappan maritime trade.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Harappa was discovered in 1921 by Daya Ram Sahni.
2. Mohenjo-daro was discovered in 1922 by R.D. Banerji.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Harappa was found in 1921 by Daya Ram Sahni and Mohenjo-daro in 1922 by R.D. Banerji.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The Harappans traded with Mesopotamia, where their land was referred to as:', 'Dilmun', 'Magan', 'Meluhha', 'Punt', 'C', 'Mesopotamian records refer to the Indus region as Meluhha.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'The Indus Valley Civilisation belonged to which technological age?', 'Iron Age', 'Copper Age only', 'Stone Age', 'Bronze Age', 'D', 'The IVC was a Bronze Age civilisation flourishing roughly 2600-1900 BCE.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Harappan script is pictographic and remains undeciphered.
2. The Pashupati seal is regarded as a proto-Shiva representation.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The pictographic Harappan script is undeciphered, and the Pashupati seal is seen as proto-Shiva.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Harappan towns were typically laid out on which pattern?', 'Radial pattern', 'Grid pattern', 'Concentric circles', 'Random clusters', 'B', 'Harappan towns followed a grid pattern with a citadel and a lower town, plus advanced drainage.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-indus-valley-civilisation', 'Which deity was widely worshipped in the Indus Valley Civilisation?', 'The Mother Goddess', 'Indra', 'Vishnu', 'Surya', 'A', 'The Harappans worshipped the Mother Goddess and a proto-Shiva Pashupati figure.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Who was the founder of the Mauryan Empire?', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Bindusara', 'Ashoka', 'Pushyamitra Shunga', 'A', 'Chandragupta Maurya founded the empire in 322 BCE with the guidance of Chanakya (Kautilya).', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Greek envoy who wrote ''Indica'' at the Mauryan court was:', 'Seleucus', 'Megasthenes', 'Fa-Hien', 'Hiuen Tsang', 'B', 'Megasthenes, the Greek envoy of Seleucus, wrote Indica at Chandragupta Maurya''s court.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Kalinga War was fought in 261 BCE.
2. After the war Ashoka propagated his policy of Dhamma.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Kalinga War of 261 BCE transformed Ashoka, who then propagated Dhamma.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Arthashastra, a treatise on statecraft, was authored by:', 'Megasthenes', 'Varahamihira', 'Harisena', 'Kautilya (Chanakya)', 'D', 'Kautilya, also known as Chanakya, authored the Arthashastra on statecraft, economy and espionage.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'The Lion Capital of Sarnath, India''s national emblem, was erected by:', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Bindusara', 'Ashoka', 'Samudragupta', 'C', 'Ashoka''s Lion Capital of Sarnath was adopted as India''s national emblem.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Ashoka''s edicts were inscribed in scripts including Brahmi and Kharosthi.
2. The Mauryan dynasty ended with the assassination of Brihadratha by Pushyamitra Shunga.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Ashoka''s edicts used Brahmi, Kharosthi, Greek and Aramaic; Pushyamitra Shunga killed Brihadratha in 185 BCE.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Which Mauryan ruler was known by the title ''Amitraghata''?', 'Bindusara', 'Chandragupta Maurya', 'Ashoka', 'Dasharatha', 'A', 'Bindusara, son of Chandragupta, was known as Amitraghata, the slayer of foes.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-mauryan-empire', 'Mauryan provinces were administered by princes who held which title?', 'Mahamatras', 'Rajukas', 'Amatyas', 'Kumaras', 'D', 'Mauryan provinces were governed by princes known as Kumaras.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Which Gupta ruler is described as the ''Napoleon of India'' by historian V.A. Smith?', 'Chandragupta I', 'Skandagupta', 'Chandragupta II', 'Samudragupta', 'D', 'Samudragupta''s extensive conquests earned him the title ''Napoleon of India'' from V.A. Smith.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'The Allahabad Pillar inscription (Prayag Prashasti) was composed by:', 'Harisena', 'Kalidasa', 'Aryabhata', 'Varahamihira', 'A', 'Harisena composed the Allahabad Pillar inscription recording Samudragupta''s conquests.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Aryabhata wrote the Aryabhatiya and proposed Earth''s rotation.
2. Fa-Hien visited India during Chandragupta II''s reign.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Aryabhata wrote the Aryabhatiya; the Chinese pilgrim Fa-Hien visited during Chandragupta II''s reign.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Chandragupta II earned fame by defeating which foreign rulers?', 'The Hunas', 'The Kushanas', 'The Shakas', 'The Greeks', 'C', 'Chandragupta II Vikramaditya defeated the Shakas, extending Gupta power to western India.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Kalidasa, the celebrated Gupta-era poet, authored which work?', 'Abhijnanashakuntalam', 'Aryabhatiya', 'Brihat Samhita', 'Indica', 'A', 'Kalidasa wrote Abhijnanashakuntalam; the Brihat Samhita was by Varahamihira.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Gupta age is called the Golden Age of India.
2. The decline of the Guptas was hastened by Huna invasions under Toramana and Mihirakula.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The Gupta age is the Golden Age; Huna invasions led by Toramana and Mihirakula hastened its decline.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'Who founded the Gupta dynasty and married Kumaradevi of the Licchavis?', 'Samudragupta', 'Chandragupta I', 'Chandragupta II', 'Sri Gupta', 'B', 'Chandragupta I founded the imperial Gupta line and strengthened it by marrying Licchavi princess Kumaradevi.', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-gupta-age', 'The Mehrauli Iron Pillar is a notable example of Gupta-era advances in:', 'Painting', 'Metallurgy', 'Astronomy', 'Town planning', 'B', 'The rust-resistant Mehrauli Iron Pillar demonstrates the high metallurgical skill of the Gupta period.', 7),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q01', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Gautama Buddha attained enlightenment at which place?', 'Lumbini', 'Sarnath', 'Kushinagar', 'Bodh Gaya', 'D', 'Buddha attained enlightenment at Bodh Gaya; he was born at Lumbini and gave his first sermon at Sarnath.', 0),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q02', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Who was the 24th and last Tirthankara of Jainism?', 'Mahavira', 'Parshvanatha', 'Neminatha', 'Rishabhanatha', 'A', 'Mahavira was the 24th Tirthankara; Rishabhanatha was the first and Parshvanatha the 23rd.', 1),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q03', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Buddha''s first sermon at Sarnath is called Dharmachakra Pravartana.
2. Buddhism follows the Middle Path.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The first sermon at Sarnath is the Dharmachakra Pravartana; Buddhism advocates the Middle Path.', 2),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q04', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The Fourth Buddhist Council, which split Buddhism into Hinayana and Mahayana, was held under:', 'Ashoka', 'Bindusara', 'Ajatashatru', 'Kanishka', 'D', 'The Fourth Buddhist Council was held under Kanishka and led to the Hinayana-Mahayana split.', 3),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q05', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The Three Jewels (Triratna) of Jainism are right faith, right knowledge and:', 'Right conduct', 'Right livelihood', 'Right speech', 'Right mindfulness', 'A', 'The Jain Triratna comprises right faith, right knowledge and right conduct.', 4),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q06', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Third Buddhist Council was held under Ashoka at Pataliputra.
2. Early Buddhist texts (Tripitaka) were written in Pali.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'The Third Council met under Ashoka at Pataliputra; the Tripitaka was composed in Pali.', 5),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q07', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The two principal sects of Jainism are:', 'Hinayana and Mahayana', 'Digambara and Svetambara', 'Theravada and Vajrayana', 'Saguna and Nirguna', 'B', 'Jainism''s two principal sects are the Digambara (sky-clad) and Svetambara (white-clad).', 6),
  ('upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism-q08', 'upsc-ancient-history-buddhism-and-jainism', 'The core ethical principle emphasised by Jainism is:', 'Idol worship', 'Moksha through ritual', 'Animal sacrifice', 'Ahimsa (non-violence)', 'D', 'Ahimsa, or non-violence, is the central ethical principle of Jainism.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Who founded the Slave (Mamluk) dynasty of the Delhi Sultanate in 1206?', 'Iltutmish', 'Qutb-ud-din Aibak', 'Balban', 'Jalal-ud-din Khalji', 'B', 'Qutb-ud-din Aibak founded the Slave dynasty in 1206 and began the Qutub Minar.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'The only woman to rule the Delhi Sultanate was:', 'Chand Bibi', 'Nur Jahan', 'Razia Sultana', 'Rani Durgavati', 'C', 'Razia Sultana, daughter of Iltutmish, was the only woman to rule the Delhi Sultanate.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Alauddin Khalji introduced market price control reforms.
2. He repelled repeated Mongol invasions.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Alauddin Khalji introduced market control reforms and successfully repelled Mongol invasions.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'The transfer of capital to Daulatabad and the issue of token currency are associated with:', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq', 'Ghiyasuddin Tughlaq', 'Muhammad bin Tughlaq', 'Bahlol Lodi', 'C', 'Muhammad bin Tughlaq shifted the capital to Daulatabad and introduced token currency.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Under the iqta system of the Delhi Sultanate, an iqta referred to:', 'A unit of currency', 'A military rank', 'An assignment of land revenue in lieu of salary', 'A religious tax', 'C', 'The iqta system assigned land revenue to officials in place of a cash salary.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Qutub Minar was begun by Qutb-ud-din Aibak and completed by Iltutmish.
2. The Delhi Sultanate ended with the First Battle of Panipat in 1526.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Aibak began and Iltutmish completed the Qutub Minar; Babur ended the Sultanate at Panipat in 1526.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Which ruler founded the Lodi dynasty, the last of the Delhi Sultanate?', 'Khizr Khan', 'Ibrahim Lodi', 'Sikandar Lodi', 'Bahlol Lodi', 'D', 'Bahlol Lodi founded the Lodi dynasty in 1451; Ibrahim Lodi was the last Sultan.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-delhi-sultanate', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq is particularly remembered for:', 'Introducing token currency', 'Defeating Babur at Panipat', 'Transferring the capital to Daulatabad', 'Levying jizya and building canals', 'D', 'Firoz Shah Tughlaq levied the jizya tax and built irrigation canals.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'The Mughal Empire was founded after the First Battle of Panipat (1526) by:', 'Humayun', 'Akbar', 'Sher Shah Suri', 'Babur', 'D', 'Babur founded the Mughal Empire after defeating Ibrahim Lodi at the First Battle of Panipat in 1526.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Who introduced the silver coin ''rupiya'' and built the Grand Trunk Road?', 'Sher Shah Suri', 'Akbar', 'Babur', 'Aurangzeb', 'A', 'Sher Shah Suri introduced the rupiya and developed the Grand Trunk Road.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Akbar abolished the jizya tax.
2. Akbar started the Din-i-Ilahi in 1582.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Akbar abolished the jizya and founded the syncretic Din-i-Ilahi in 1582.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'The Zabti or Dahsala revenue system was developed under Akbar by:', 'Birbal', 'Abul Fazl', 'Raja Todar Mal', 'Man Singh', 'C', 'Raja Todar Mal developed the Zabti (Dahsala) land revenue system under Akbar.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'In the Mansabdari system, the ranks ''zat'' and ''sawar'' indicated respectively:', 'Tax rate and revenue share', 'Land grant and salary', 'Religious rank and military rank', 'Personal status and cavalry obligation', 'D', 'Zat denoted personal status and pay, while sawar indicated the number of cavalry to be maintained.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal.
2. Mughal painting peaked under Jahangir.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal and Mughal painting reached its zenith under Jahangir.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Which Mughal emperor re-imposed the jizya and expanded the empire to its greatest extent?', 'Akbar', 'Jahangir', 'Aurangzeb', 'Shah Jahan', 'C', 'Aurangzeb re-imposed the jizya and took the empire to its greatest territorial extent.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-mughal-empire', 'Mughal emperor Humayun is best known for:', 'Building Fatehpur Sikri', 'Starting the Din-i-Ilahi', 'Losing his throne to Sher Shah Suri', 'Building the Taj Mahal', 'C', 'Humayun temporarily lost the throne to Sher Shah Suri before regaining it in 1555.', 7),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q01', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Which saint founded Sikhism?', 'Guru Nanak', 'Ramananda', 'Kabir', 'Chaitanya', 'A', 'Guru Nanak founded Sikhism; he was a Nirguna saint who rejected ritualism and caste.', 0),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q02', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Bhakti saint Mirabai was devoted to:', 'Krishna', 'Shiva', 'Rama', 'Vishnu as Vithoba', 'A', 'Mirabai of Rajasthan was a devotee of Krishna and a celebrated Bhakti poet.', 1),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q03', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Kabir and Guru Nanak were Nirguna saints.
2. Saguna saints worshipped a god with form.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Kabir and Guru Nanak belonged to the Nirguna (formless) school; Saguna saints worshipped a god with form.', 2),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q04', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Chishti Sufi order in India is most closely associated with which saint of Ajmer?', 'Nizamuddin Auliya', 'Sheikh Bahauddin Zakariya', 'Baba Farid', 'Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti', 'D', 'Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti of Ajmer founded the influential Chishti order in India.', 3),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q05', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'In Sufi tradition, a ''khanqah'' refers to:', 'A Sufi hospice', 'A devotional song', 'A mystical order', 'A holy relic', 'A', 'A khanqah was a Sufi hospice where the saint lived and disciples gathered.', 4),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q06', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Sufi orders were organised into silsilas.
2. Sama, or devotional music, was central to the Chishti order.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Sufism was organised into silsilas (orders), and Sama (devotional music) was central to the Chishtis.', 5),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q07', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The Bhakti saint Chaitanya is chiefly associated with which region?', 'Rajasthan', 'Awadh', 'Bengal', 'Maharashtra', 'C', 'Chaitanya Mahaprabhu spread Krishna devotion in Bengal and Odisha.', 6),
  ('upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements-q08', 'upsc-medieval-history-bhakti-and-sufi-movements', 'The poet and musician closely associated with Nizamuddin Auliya was:', 'Tulsidas', 'Kabir', 'Amir Khusro', 'Surdas', 'C', 'Amir Khusro, a disciple of Nizamuddin Auliya, contributed greatly to a composite Indo-Islamic culture.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The curvilinear shikhara is the defining feature of which temple style?', 'Dravida', 'Nagara', 'Vesara', 'Kalinga only', 'B', 'The Nagara style of north India is marked by a curvilinear shikhara and lacks boundary walls.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The gopuram, a towering gateway, is a characteristic feature of which style?', 'Nagara', 'Bengal terracotta', 'Vesara', 'Dravida', 'D', 'The Dravida temple of south India is enclosed by walls with a gopuram gateway tower.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Brihadeshwara Temple at Thanjavur was built by the Cholas.
2. The Kandariya Mahadeva at Khajuraho is a Nagara temple.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The Chola Brihadeshwara Temple is Dravida; Khajuraho''s Kandariya Mahadeva is a Nagara temple.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'In temple architecture, the ''garbhagriha'' is the:', 'Assembly hall', 'Circumambulatory path', 'Gateway tower', 'Sanctum housing the deity', 'D', 'The garbhagriha is the sanctum sanctorum that houses the main deity; the mandapa is the assembly hall.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The monolithic Kailasa Temple at Ellora was carved by which dynasty?', 'Cholas', 'Rashtrakutas', 'Pallavas', 'Hoysalas', 'B', 'The Rashtrakutas carved the monolithic Kailasa Temple at Ellora from top to bottom.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Vesara style is a hybrid associated with the Chalukyas and Hoysalas.
2. The shore temple and rathas at Mahabalipuram were built by the Pallavas.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Vesara is a hybrid style of the Chalukyas and Hoysalas; Mahabalipuram''s monuments are Pallava works.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The Sun Temple at Konark is an example of which architectural style?', 'Dravida', 'Vesara', 'Nagara', 'Indo-Saracenic', 'C', 'The Sun Temple at Konark is a famous Nagara-style temple in Odisha.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-temple-architecture', 'The amalaka and kalasha typically crown the tower of which temple style?', 'Nagara', 'Dravida', 'Vesara', 'Cave temples', 'A', 'The amalaka and kalasha crown the shikhara of a Nagara-style temple.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'How many dance forms are officially recognised as classical in India?', 'Six', 'Seven', 'Nine', 'Eight', 'D', 'India recognises eight classical dance forms, each rooted in Bharata''s Natya Shastra.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Which classical dance form originates from Kerala and uses elaborate make-up and masks?', 'Kuchipudi', 'Manipuri', 'Odissi', 'Kathakali', 'D', 'Kathakali of Kerala uses elaborate make-up and masks to depict episodes from the epics.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Bharatanatyam is the oldest classical dance and originated in temples.
2. Kathak shows strong Persian and Mughal influence.
Which is/are correct?', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Bharatanatyam is the oldest temple dance, and Kathak carries strong Persian and Mughal influence.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Sattriya, a classical dance form, originated in which state?', 'Odisha', 'Manipur', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Assam', 'D', 'Sattriya originated in Assam and was founded by the Vaishnavite saint Sankaradeva.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Mohiniyattam, a solo female dance embodying Lasya grace, belongs to:', 'Kerala', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Odisha', 'Karnataka', 'A', 'Mohiniyattam is a graceful solo female dance form from Kerala embodying the Lasya aspect.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Tandava is the vigorous, masculine aspect of dance.
2. Lasya is the graceful, feminine aspect of dance.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Tandava is the vigorous masculine aspect and Lasya the graceful feminine aspect of dance.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'The foundational treatise on Indian performing arts is the:', 'Abhinaya Darpana only', 'Arthashastra', 'Natya Shastra', 'Sangeet Ratnakara', 'C', 'Bharata''s Natya Shastra is the foundational treatise underpinning India''s classical dance forms.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-classical-dance-forms', 'Manipuri dance is best known for its gentle devotional movements linked to:', 'Raslila', 'Tandava', 'The devadasi tradition', 'Mughal courts', 'A', 'Manipuri dance is known for its gentle, devotional movements linked to the Raslila of Krishna.', 7),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q01', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The Ajanta cave murals were executed primarily in which technique?', 'Fresco buono', 'Watercolour wash', 'Oil painting', 'Tempera', 'D', 'The Buddhist murals of Ajanta were painted in the tempera technique.', 0),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q02', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The famous ''Bani Thani'' portrait belongs to which school of painting?', 'Pahari (Kangra)', 'Mughal', 'Deccan', 'Kishangarh', 'D', 'The Bani Thani portrait is the signature work of the Kishangarh school of Rajasthani painting.', 1),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q03', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Madhubani painting originates from Bihar.
2. Warli painting uses white figures on a mud background.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'Madhubani (Mithila) painting is from Bihar; Warli painting uses white figures on a mud background.', 2),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q04', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Mughal painting reached its zenith under which emperor?', 'Akbar', 'Jahangir', 'Shah Jahan', 'Humayun', 'B', 'Mughal painting, blending Persian technique with Indian themes, peaked under Jahangir.', 3),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q05', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Pattachitra, a cloth-based scroll painting, is traditionally associated with:', 'Maharashtra', 'Bihar', 'Odisha and Bengal', 'Rajasthan', 'C', 'Pattachitra is a cloth-based scroll painting tradition of Odisha and Bengal.', 4),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q06', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Bengal School was led by Abanindranath Tagore.
2. It revived Indian themes against Western academic art.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Abanindranath Tagore led the Bengal School, which revived Indian themes against Western academic art.', 5),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q07', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'Which of the following is a Pahari school of miniature painting?', 'Bundi', 'Bijapur', 'Kangra', 'Mewar', 'C', 'Kangra and Basohli are Pahari schools; Bundi and Mewar are Rajasthani and Bijapur is Deccan.', 6),
  ('upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools-q08', 'upsc-art-and-culture-indian-painting-schools', 'The Deccan school of miniature painting flourished at which centres?', 'Kangra and Basohli', 'Mewar and Bundi', 'Bijapur and Golconda', 'Mithila and Tanjore', 'C', 'The Deccan school flourished at Bijapur and Golconda.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q01', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The largest peninsular river of India, called the ''Dakshin Ganga'', is the:', 'Godavari', 'Kaveri', 'Krishna', 'Mahanadi', 'A', 'The Godavari is the largest peninsular river and is known as the Dakshin Ganga.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q02', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Which two rivers flow westward through rift valleys into the Arabian Sea?', 'Godavari and Krishna', 'Narmada and Tapi', 'Ganga and Yamuna', 'Mahanadi and Kaveri', 'B', 'The Narmada and Tapi flow westward through rift valleys into the Arabian Sea.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q03', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Indus and Brahmaputra are antecedent rivers.
2. They are older than the Himalayas.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Indus and Brahmaputra are antecedent rivers older than the Himalayas through which they cut.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q04', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The highest peak of peninsular India is:', 'K2 (Godwin Austen)', 'Doda Betta', 'Anamudi', 'Mahendragiri', 'C', 'Anamudi, in the Western Ghats, is the highest peak of peninsular India.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q05', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The three parallel ranges of the Himalayas from north to south are:', 'Shiwaliks, Himachal, Himadri', 'Himadri, Himachal, Shiwaliks', 'Himachal, Himadri, Shiwaliks', 'Himadri, Shiwaliks, Himachal', 'B', 'From north to south the ranges are the Himadri (Greater), Himachal (Lesser) and Shiwaliks (Outer).', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q06', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Peninsular Plateau is the oldest landmass made of Gondwana rocks.
2. The Western Ghats are continuous and higher than the Eastern Ghats.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'The Peninsular Plateau is the oldest Gondwana landmass, and the Western Ghats are continuous and higher.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q07', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'The highest peak located within India is:', 'Mount Everest', 'K2 (Godwin Austen)', 'Kanchenjunga', 'Nanda Devi', 'B', 'K2, also called Godwin Austen, is the highest peak in India (in the Karakoram range).', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers-q08', 'upsc-geography-indian-physiography-and-rivers', 'Himalayan rivers are generally described as perennial because they are fed by:', 'Only the monsoon', 'Both glaciers and rainfall', 'Only groundwater', 'Only lakes', 'B', 'Himalayan rivers are perennial because they receive water from both melting glaciers and rainfall.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q01', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Black soil (regur) is especially suited to the cultivation of:', 'Tea', 'Cotton', 'Rice', 'Coffee', 'B', 'Black soil, or regur, retains moisture well and is ideal for cotton, hence ''black cotton soil''.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q02', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'In the alluvial soils of India, the older alluvium is known as:', 'Khadar', 'Laterite', 'Regur', 'Bhangar', 'D', 'Bhangar is old alluvium while khadar is the newer, more fertile alluvium.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q03', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Kharif crops are sown in June-July.
2. Rabi crops include wheat and gram.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Kharif crops are sown in June-July; rabi crops such as wheat and gram are sown in winter.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q04', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'The White Revolution in India is associated with:', 'Foodgrains', 'Oilseeds', 'Fisheries', 'Milk production', 'D', 'The White Revolution (Operation Flood) under Verghese Kurien boosted milk production.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q05', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Laterite soil, formed by leaching, is best suited to which crops?', 'Wheat and sugarcane', 'Cotton and gram', 'Mustard and pulses', 'Tea, coffee and cashew', 'D', 'Leached, acidic laterite soil suits plantation crops like tea, coffee and cashew.', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q06', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Green Revolution was associated with M.S. Swaminathan and Norman Borlaug.
2. Alluvial soil covers about 40% of India''s land.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Swaminathan and Borlaug led the Green Revolution; alluvial soil covers roughly 40% of India''s land.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q07', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'Which cropping season corresponds to the short summer period?', 'Kharif', 'Zaid', 'Rabi', 'Bhangar', 'B', 'The Zaid season is the short summer cropping period for crops like watermelon and cucumber.', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture-q08', 'upsc-geography-soils-and-agriculture', 'The Blue Revolution in India refers to development in:', 'Oilseeds', 'Milk', 'Fisheries', 'Foodgrains', 'C', 'The Blue Revolution refers to the development of fisheries and aquaculture.', 7),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q01', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The theory of Continental Drift was proposed by:', 'Alfred Wegener', 'Charles Lyell', 'James Hutton', 'Harry Hess', 'A', 'Alfred Wegener proposed the Continental Drift theory, a precursor to plate tectonics.', 0),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q02', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Mid-ocean ridges and rift valleys are typically formed at which plate boundary?', 'Convergent', 'Divergent', 'Transform', 'Subduction', 'B', 'Divergent boundaries, where plates move apart, create mid-ocean ridges and rift valleys.', 1),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q03', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Himalayas formed by the convergence of the Indian and Eurasian plates.
2. The Pacific Ring of Fire hosts about two-thirds of the world''s active volcanoes.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The Himalayas arose from Indian-Eurasian convergence; the Ring of Fire holds about two-thirds of active volcanoes.', 2),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q04', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The San Andreas Fault is a classic example of which type of plate boundary?', 'Transform', 'Divergent', 'Convergent', 'Continental', 'A', 'The San Andreas Fault is a transform boundary where plates slide past one another, causing earthquakes.', 3),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q05', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The highest plateau in the world is the:', 'Tibetan Plateau', 'Deccan Plateau', 'Colorado Plateau', 'Ethiopian Plateau', 'A', 'The Tibetan Plateau is the highest plateau in the world.', 4),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q06', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Block mountains are formed by horst and graben structures.
2. The Himalayas and Andes are examples of fold mountains.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'Block mountains arise from horst-and-graben faulting; the Himalayas and Andes are fold mountains.', 5),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q07', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'Forces originating from within the Earth that shape landforms are called:', 'Exogenic forces', 'Aeolian forces', 'Gradational forces', 'Endogenic forces', 'D', 'Endogenic (internal) forces such as tectonics build landforms; exogenic forces wear them down.', 6),
  ('upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms-q08', 'upsc-geography-world-geography-landforms', 'The outermost layer of the Earth, broken into tectonic plates, is the:', 'Mantle', 'Lithosphere', 'Outer core', 'Asthenosphere', 'B', 'The lithosphere is the rigid outer layer of the Earth that is broken into tectonic plates.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q01', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Gross Domestic Product (GDP) measures the value of final goods and services produced:', 'By a country''s nationals worldwide', 'Only in the manufacturing sector', 'Within a country''s borders', 'After deducting depreciation', 'C', 'GDP is the value of all final goods and services produced within a country''s borders in a year.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q02', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Gross National Product (GNP) is equal to:', 'GDP plus net factor income from abroad', 'GDP minus depreciation', 'GDP plus depreciation', 'NNP plus taxes', 'A', 'GNP equals GDP plus net factor income from abroad (NFIA).', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q03', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Nominal GDP is calculated at current prices.
2. Real GDP is calculated at constant base-year prices.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'Nominal GDP uses current prices, while real GDP uses constant base-year prices.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q04', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'The current base year for India''s GDP estimates is:', '2004-05', '2015-16', '2011-12', '2020-21', 'C', 'India''s GDP series uses 2011-12 as the base year, with figures released by the NSO under MoSPI.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q05', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'The GDP deflator is calculated as:', '(Real GDP / Nominal GDP) x 100', 'Nominal GDP minus Real GDP', '(Nominal GDP / Real GDP) x 100', 'GDP minus depreciation', 'C', 'The GDP deflator equals Nominal GDP divided by Real GDP, multiplied by 100.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q06', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Consider the following statements:
1. NNP at factor cost is termed the National Income.
2. Per capita income equals National Income divided by population.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'NNP at factor cost is the National Income, and per capita income is National Income divided by population.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q07', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Net Domestic Product (NDP) is obtained by:', 'Adding NFIA to GDP', 'Subtracting taxes from GNP', 'Adding depreciation to GDP', 'Subtracting depreciation from GDP', 'D', 'NDP equals GDP minus depreciation.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp-q08', 'upsc-economy-national-income-and-gdp', 'Which of the following is NOT one of the three methods of measuring national income?', 'Production (value-added) method', 'Income method', 'Depreciation method', 'Expenditure method', 'C', 'National income is measured by the production, income and expenditure methods, not a ''depreciation method''.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q01', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'In which year was the Reserve Bank of India nationalised?', '1935', '1947', '1969', '1949', 'D', 'The RBI was established in 1935 and nationalised in 1949.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q02', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The ''repo rate'' is the rate at which:', 'Banks lend to the RBI', 'The RBI lends to commercial banks', 'Banks lend to each other', 'The government borrows from the public', 'B', 'The repo rate is the rate at which the RBI lends short-term funds to commercial banks.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q03', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The RBI is the sole issuer of currency except the one-rupee note and coins.
2. The RBI is the lender of last resort to banks.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The RBI issues currency except the one-rupee note and coins, and acts as lender of last resort.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q04', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'An asset is classified as a Non-Performing Asset (NPA) if interest or principal is overdue for:', '30 days', '60 days', '90 days', '180 days', 'C', 'A loan becomes an NPA when interest or principal remains overdue for 90 days.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q05', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The one-rupee note and coins in India are issued by:', 'The Reserve Bank of India', 'The Ministry of Finance', 'The State Bank of India', 'NABARD', 'B', 'The one-rupee note and coins are issued by the Ministry of Finance, not the RBI.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q06', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The SLR is capped at 40%.
2. Scheduled commercial banks are listed in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'SLR is capped at 40% and scheduled commercial banks are listed in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q07', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'Which of the following is true of Payments Banks in India?', 'They can issue credit cards', 'They can give long-term loans', 'They cannot lend or issue credit cards', 'They function only in rural areas', 'C', 'Payments Banks accept small deposits but cannot lend or issue credit cards.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi-q08', 'upsc-economy-banking-system-and-rbi', 'The Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) was enacted in which year?', '2013', '2016', '2014', '2018', 'B', 'The Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code was enacted in 2016 to speed up resolution of bad loans.', 7),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q01', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Union Budget is presented as the ''Annual Financial Statement'' under which Article?', 'Article 112', 'Article 110', 'Article 266', 'Article 280', 'A', 'Article 112 provides for the Annual Financial Statement, that is, the Union Budget.', 0),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q02', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Fiscal Deficit is best defined as:', 'Revenue Expenditure minus Revenue Receipts', 'Total Expenditure minus Total Receipts excluding borrowings', 'Fiscal Deficit minus Interest Payments', 'Capital Receipts minus Capital Expenditure', 'B', 'The Fiscal Deficit equals total expenditure minus total receipts excluding borrowings, indicating borrowing needs.', 1),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q03', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Primary Deficit equals the Fiscal Deficit minus interest payments.
2. The FRBM Act was enacted in 2003.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The Primary Deficit is the Fiscal Deficit minus interest payments; the FRBM Act was passed in 2003.', 2),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q04', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The Goods and Services Tax (GST) was launched in India on:', '1 April 2016', '26 January 2017', '1 January 2018', '1 July 2017', 'D', 'GST, a destination-based tax, was launched on 1 July 2017 and is governed by the GST Council.', 3),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q05', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'The GST Council is a constitutional body created under which Article?', 'Article 112', 'Article 110', 'Article 279A', 'Article 266', 'C', 'The GST Council is established under Article 279A of the Constitution.', 4),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q06', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Direct taxes are progressive.
2. Indirect taxes such as GST are regressive.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Direct taxes like income tax are progressive, while indirect taxes such as GST are regressive.', 5),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q07', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'All revenues received by the Government of India are credited to the:', 'Contingency Fund', 'Public Account', 'Capital Account', 'Consolidated Fund of India', 'D', 'The Consolidated Fund of India (Article 266) holds all government revenues; withdrawals need parliamentary approval.', 6),
  ('upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy-q08', 'upsc-economy-union-budget-and-fiscal-policy', 'Which of the following is a revenue receipt of the government?', 'Tax revenue', 'Disinvestment proceeds', 'Borrowings', 'Recovery of loans', 'A', 'Tax revenue is a non-debt-creating revenue receipt; borrowings and disinvestment are capital receipts.', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q01', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'How many biodiversity hotspots are located in India?', 'Two', 'Four', 'Three', 'Six', 'B', 'India has four biodiversity hotspots: the Himalayas, Western Ghats, Indo-Burma and Sundaland.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q02', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Conservation of species within their natural habitat is known as:', 'In-situ conservation', 'Ex-situ conservation', 'Cryopreservation', 'Captive breeding', 'A', 'In-situ conservation protects species in their natural habitat, such as national parks and sanctuaries.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q03', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. National Parks allow no human activity.
2. Wildlife Sanctuaries permit some regulated activity.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'National Parks prohibit human activity while Sanctuaries permit certain regulated activities.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q04', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Project Tiger was launched in which year?', '1972', '1992', '1985', '1973', 'D', 'Project Tiger was launched in 1973; Project Elephant followed in 1992.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q05', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'The Convention on Biological Diversity (CBD) was adopted at which summit?', 'Stockholm Conference 1972', 'Johannesburg Summit 2002', 'Rio Earth Summit 1992', 'Paris Summit 2015', 'C', 'The CBD was adopted at the Rio Earth Summit in 1992.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q06', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India is one of 17 megadiverse countries.
2. Biosphere Reserves have core, buffer and transition zones.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'India is among 17 megadiverse nations, and Biosphere Reserves comprise core, buffer and transition zones.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q07', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Protected species in India are listed in the schedules of which Act?', 'Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972', 'Environment Protection Act, 1986', 'Forest Conservation Act, 1980', 'Biological Diversity Act, 2002', 'A', 'The Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972 lists protected species in its schedules.', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation-q08', 'upsc-environment-biodiversity-and-conservation', 'Which international convention regulates trade in endangered species?', 'CBD', 'Ramsar Convention', 'CITES', 'UNFCCC', 'C', 'CITES regulates international trade in endangered species of wild fauna and flora.', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q01', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Paris Agreement (2015) aims to limit the rise in global average temperature to:', 'Below 3 degrees C', 'Well below 2 degrees C, pursuing 1.5 degrees C', 'Exactly 2.5 degrees C', 'Below 4 degrees C', 'B', 'The Paris Agreement seeks to keep warming well below 2 degrees C while pursuing 1.5 degrees C.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q02', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Montreal Protocol (1987) was aimed at phasing out:', 'Greenhouse gases', 'Fossil fuel subsidies', 'Ozone-depleting substances', 'Plastic waste', 'C', 'The Montreal Protocol phased out ozone-depleting substances; its Kigali Amendment targets HFCs.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q03', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The IPCC was set up in 1988 by WMO and UNEP.
2. The UNFCCC of 1992 is the parent climate treaty.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'The IPCC was set up in 1988 by WMO and UNEP, and the 1992 UNFCCC is the parent climate treaty.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q04', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'India has set a target of achieving net zero emissions by:', '2050', '2060', '2070', '2047', 'C', 'India targets net zero emissions by 2070, following the principle of CBDR.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q05', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'The Kyoto Protocol of 1997 set binding emission targets primarily for:', 'Developing nations', 'Only island nations', 'All UN members equally', 'Developed nations', 'D', 'The Kyoto Protocol set binding greenhouse gas targets for developed nations.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q06', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Methane is mainly emitted by livestock, paddy and landfills.
2. The Paris Agreement operates through Nationally Determined Contributions.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Methane comes from livestock, paddy and landfills; the Paris Agreement works through NDCs.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q07', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'Parties to the UNFCCC meet annually at the:', 'Conference of the Parties (COP)', 'General Assembly', 'Security Council', 'G20 Summit', 'A', 'Parties to the UNFCCC meet annually at the Conference of the Parties (COP).', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements-q08', 'upsc-environment-climate-change-and-global-agreements', 'India''s climate missions are coordinated under which national framework?', 'FRBM', 'NITI Aayog', 'NAPCC', 'NDB', 'C', 'India''s climate missions operate under the National Action Plan on Climate Change (NAPCC).', 7),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q01', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'In an ecosystem, green plants are classified as:', 'Primary consumers', 'Decomposers', 'Producers', 'Secondary consumers', 'C', 'Green plants are autotrophic producers that fix energy at the base of the food chain.', 0),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q02', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'According to Lindeman''s 10% law, the energy transferred to the next trophic level is about:', '1%', '10%', '50%', '90%', 'B', 'Lindeman''s 10% law states that only about 10% of energy is transferred to the next trophic level.', 1),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q03', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Energy flow in an ecosystem is unidirectional.
2. The pyramid of energy is always upright.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'Energy flow is unidirectional and the energy pyramid is always upright.', 2),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q04', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Which of the following are decomposers in an ecosystem?', 'Bacteria and fungi', 'Carnivores', 'Herbivores', 'Green plants', 'A', 'Bacteria and fungi act as decomposers, breaking down dead organic matter.', 3),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q05', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'An interconnected network of food chains is called a:', 'Ecological niche', 'Trophic level', 'Biome', 'Food web', 'D', 'A food web is an interconnected network of multiple food chains.', 4),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q06', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Net Primary Productivity equals GPP minus respiration.
2. NPP is the energy available to consumers.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'NPP equals GPP minus respiration and represents the energy available to consumers.', 5),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q07', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Which of the following is an abiotic component of an ecosystem?', 'Herbivores', 'Decomposers', 'Producers', 'Sunlight', 'D', 'Sunlight, water, soil and temperature are abiotic (non-living) components of an ecosystem.', 6),
  ('upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains-q08', 'upsc-environment-ecosystems-and-food-chains', 'Herbivores in a food chain occupy the trophic level of:', 'Primary consumers', 'Producers', 'Secondary consumers', 'Decomposers', 'A', 'Herbivores feed on producers and so occupy the primary consumer trophic level.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Who is regarded as the father of the Indian space programme?', 'A.P.J. Abdul Kalam', 'Satish Dhawan', 'Vikram Sarabhai', 'Homi Bhabha', 'C', 'Vikram Sarabhai, under whom ISRO was founded in 1969, is the father of the Indian space programme.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'India''s first satellite, launched in 1975, was named:', 'Bhaskara', 'Rohini', 'Aryabhata', 'INSAT-1A', 'C', 'Aryabhata, launched in 1975, was India''s first satellite.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The PSLV is known as the workhorse of ISRO.
2. The GSLV uses an indigenous cryogenic upper stage.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'The PSLV is ISRO''s workhorse, and the GSLV uses an indigenous cryogenic upper stage.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Which Indian mission made India the first nation to reach Mars orbit on its first attempt?', 'Mangalyaan (Mars Orbiter Mission)', 'Chandrayaan-1', 'Aditya-L1', 'Gaganyaan', 'A', 'Mangalyaan (2013) made India the first nation to reach Mars orbit on its first attempt.', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Chandrayaan-3 (2023) is notable for soft-landing near the Moon''s:', 'North pole', 'Equator', 'South pole', 'Far side centre', 'C', 'Chandrayaan-3 soft-landed near the lunar south pole in 2023.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Chandrayaan-1 discovered water molecules on the Moon.
2. NavIC is India''s regional satellite navigation system.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Chandrayaan-1 found water molecules on the Moon, and NavIC (IRNSS) is India''s regional navigation system.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'The Aditya-L1 mission is designed to study the:', 'Sun', 'Mars', 'Moon', 'Venus', 'A', 'Aditya-L1 studies the Sun from the L1 Lagrange point.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-space-technology-isro', 'Gaganyaan is India''s planned mission for:', 'Its first crewed spaceflight', 'A Mars rover', 'A lunar sample return', 'An asteroid mission', 'A', 'Gaganyaan aims to achieve India''s first crewed spaceflight.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which enzymes are used to cut DNA at specific recognition sites?', 'Restriction enzymes', 'DNA ligases', 'Polymerases', 'Helicases', 'A', 'Restriction enzymes cut DNA at specific sequences, a key tool in genetic engineering.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The technique used to amplify copies of a DNA segment is:', 'Electrophoresis', 'Chromatography', 'PCR (Polymerase Chain Reaction)', 'Centrifugation', 'C', 'PCR (Polymerase Chain Reaction) amplifies copies of a specific DNA segment.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Bt cotton is India''s only approved GM crop for commercial cultivation.
2. Golden Rice is engineered to be rich in Vitamin A.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'Bt cotton is India''s only approved commercial GM crop, and Golden Rice is engineered for Vitamin A.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which body in India approves the release of genetically modified organisms?', 'ICMR', 'DBT', 'GEAC', 'CSIR', 'C', 'The Genetic Engineering Appraisal Committee (GEAC) under the MoEFCC approves GM organisms.', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The revolutionary precise gene-editing tool widely used in biotechnology is:', 'PCR', 'CRISPR-Cas9', 'Gel electrophoresis', 'Plasmid cloning', 'B', 'CRISPR-Cas9 is a revolutionary tool for precise gene editing.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Consider the following statements:
1. Plasmids are used as vectors to carry genes into cells.
2. Bt cotton resists bollworm pests.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'Plasmids serve as vectors carrying genes into cells, and Bt cotton resists bollworm pests.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'The insertion, deletion or modification of genes using recombinant DNA is called:', 'Tissue culture', 'Genetic engineering', 'Fermentation', 'Hybridisation', 'B', 'Genetic engineering modifies genes using recombinant DNA technology.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-biotechnology-basics', 'Which of the following is commonly produced using biotechnology?', 'Steel', 'Cement', 'Petroleum', 'Insulin', 'D', 'Insulin, vaccines and monoclonal antibodies are produced using biotechnology.', 7),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q01', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) was established in:', '1947', '1958', '1969', '1974', 'B', 'DRDO was established in 1958 to make India''s armed forces self-reliant in technology.', 0),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q02', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Integrated Guided Missile Development Programme (IGMDP) was led by:', 'A.P.J. Abdul Kalam', 'Homi Bhabha', 'Vikram Sarabhai', 'Satish Dhawan', 'A', 'Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam led the IGMDP, earning the title ''Missile Man of India''.', 1),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q03', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Consider the following statements:
1. BrahMos is an India-Russia joint venture cruise missile.
2. Akash is a surface-to-air missile.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'BrahMos is an India-Russia supersonic cruise missile and Akash is a surface-to-air missile.', 2),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q04', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Tejas is India''s indigenous:', 'Main battle tank', 'Light Combat Aircraft', 'Nuclear submarine', 'Aircraft carrier', 'B', 'Tejas is India''s indigenous Light Combat Aircraft (LCA).', 3),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q05', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'INS Arihant is significant as India''s:', 'First aircraft carrier', 'Largest destroyer', 'First nuclear-powered submarine', 'First frigate', 'C', 'INS Arihant is India''s first indigenous nuclear-powered ballistic missile submarine, completing the nuclear triad.', 4),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q06', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India follows a No First Use nuclear doctrine.
2. INS Vikrant is India''s first indigenous aircraft carrier.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '2 only', 'B', 'India follows a No First Use doctrine, and INS Vikrant is its first indigenous aircraft carrier.', 5),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q07', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Agni series of missiles are classified as:', 'Surface-to-air missiles', 'Anti-tank missiles', 'Surface-to-surface ballistic missiles', 'Cruise missiles', 'C', 'Agni missiles are surface-to-surface ballistic missiles.', 6),
  ('upsc-science-technology-defence-technology-q08', 'upsc-science-technology-defence-technology', 'The Nag missile developed by DRDO is a:', 'Surface-to-air missile', 'Cruise missile', 'Intercontinental ballistic missile', 'Anti-tank guided missile', 'D', 'The Nag is an anti-tank guided missile developed under the IGMDP.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'With which country does India share its longest land border?', 'China', 'Pakistan', 'Nepal', 'Bangladesh', 'D', 'India shares its longest land border with Bangladesh.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The boundary line between India and China in the eastern sector is the:', 'Radcliffe Line', 'McMahon Line', 'Durand Line', 'Line of Control', 'B', 'The McMahon Line demarcates the India-China boundary in the eastern sector.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Chabahar Port is located in Iran.
2. It helps India reach Afghanistan and Central Asia bypassing Pakistan.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'B', 'The Chabahar Port in Iran lets India reach Afghanistan and Central Asia while bypassing Pakistan.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The ''SAGAR'' doctrine relates to India''s policy in which domain?', 'Cyber security', 'Maritime security and growth', 'Space cooperation', 'Trade tariffs', 'B', 'SAGAR (Security and Growth for All in the Region) guides India''s maritime policy in the Indian Ocean.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The Kalapani territorial dispute is between India and:', 'China', 'Bhutan', 'Myanmar', 'Nepal', 'D', 'The Kalapani dispute is a boundary issue between India and Nepal.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Land Boundary Agreement with Bangladesh was implemented in 2015.
2. India and China are separated by the Line of Actual Control.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The India-Bangladesh Land Boundary Agreement took effect in 2015; India and China are divided by the LAC.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'The Gujral Doctrine emphasised:', 'Non-reciprocal accommodation of smaller neighbours', 'Strict reciprocity with all neighbours', 'Military alliances in South Asia', 'Economic sanctions on rivals', 'A', 'The Gujral Doctrine emphasised non-reciprocal accommodation of India''s smaller neighbours.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-india-and-its-neighbours', 'India''s broad approach toward its immediate neighbours is captured by which policy?', 'Look East Policy', 'Indo-Pacific Strategy', 'Connect Central Asia Policy', 'Neighbourhood First Policy', 'D', 'India''s approach to its immediate neighbours is guided by the ''Neighbourhood First'' policy.', 7),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q01', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Which countries make up the QUAD grouping?', 'India, US, UK, France', 'India, China, Russia, Brazil', 'India, US, Japan, Australia', 'India, Japan, Israel, UAE', 'C', 'The QUAD comprises India, the United States, Japan and Australia.', 0),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q02', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The New Development Bank (NDB) of BRICS is headquartered in:', 'Shanghai', 'New Delhi', 'Moscow', 'Johannesburg', 'A', 'The BRICS New Development Bank is headquartered in Shanghai.', 1),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q03', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements:
1. SAARC was established in 1985 with its secretariat at Kathmandu.
2. ASEAN is central to India''s Act East policy.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'SAARC was set up in 1985 with its secretariat in Kathmandu; ASEAN anchors India''s Act East policy.', 2),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q04', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The I2U2 grouping comprises India, Israel, the USA and:', 'Saudi Arabia', 'Qatar', 'Egypt', 'The United Arab Emirates', 'D', 'I2U2 groups India, Israel, the United Arab Emirates and the United States.', 3),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q05', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'India hosted the G20 summit in which year?', '2021', '2023', '2022', '2024', 'B', 'India hosted the G20 summit in 2023.', 4),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q06', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements:
1. India is a member of the MTCR.
2. India is a member of the Nuclear Suppliers Group (NSG).
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'C', 'India is a member of the MTCR but is not yet a member of the Nuclear Suppliers Group.', 5),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q07', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'The grouping linking the countries around the Bay of Bengal is:', 'SAARC', 'BIMSTEC', 'ASEAN', 'SCO', 'B', 'BIMSTEC links South Asian and Southeast Asian nations around the Bay of Bengal.', 6),
  ('upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings-q08', 'upsc-international-relations-major-global-groupings', 'Consider the following statements about India''s global standing:
1. India is a founding member of the United Nations (1945).
2. India is a permanent member of the UN Security Council.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Both 1 and 2', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'India is a founding UN member of 1945 but is not a permanent member of the Security Council.', 7),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q01', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Human Development Index (HDI) is published by which organisation?', 'World Bank', 'IMF', 'WEF', 'UNDP', 'D', 'The HDI is published annually by the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP).', 0),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q02', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Global Innovation Index is released by:', 'UNESCO', 'WTO', 'WHO', 'WIPO', 'D', 'The Global Innovation Index is released by the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO).', 1),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q03', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'Consider the following statements:
1. NITI Aayog replaced the Planning Commission in 2015.
2. The HDI combines life expectancy, education and per capita income.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', '1 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'A', 'NITI Aayog replaced the Planning Commission in 2015; the HDI combines longevity, education and income.', 2),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q04', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The ''World Economic Outlook'' is published by which institution?', 'World Bank', 'OECD', 'WEF', 'IMF', 'D', 'The International Monetary Fund (IMF) publishes the World Economic Outlook.', 3),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q05', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The Global Gender Gap Report is released by the:', 'World Economic Forum', 'World Bank', 'UNDP', 'WHO', 'A', 'The World Economic Forum (WEF) releases the Global Gender Gap Report.', 4),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q06', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Multidimensional Poverty Index is published jointly by UNDP and OPHI.
2. The Environmental Performance Index is released by Yale and Columbia universities.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The MPI is published by UNDP and OPHI; the EPI is released by Yale and Columbia universities.', 5),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q07', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The World Development Report is published by:', 'The IMF', 'The UNDP', 'The WTO', 'The World Bank', 'D', 'The World Bank publishes the World Development Report.', 6),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices-q08', 'upsc-current-affairs-key-institutions-and-indices', 'The World Happiness Report is published under the auspices of the:', 'WHO', 'World Bank', 'Sustainable Development Solutions Network (SDSN)', 'OECD', 'C', 'The World Happiness Report is released by the UN''s Sustainable Development Solutions Network (SDSN).', 7),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q01', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Anti-defection disqualifications are decided by whom under the Tenth Schedule?', 'The President', 'The Presiding Officer of the House', 'The Supreme Court', 'The Election Commission', 'B', 'Under the Tenth Schedule, the Presiding Officer of the House decides anti-defection disqualifications.', 0),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q02', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'The Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) was established in:', '1988', '1991', '1992', '2000', 'C', 'SEBI was given statutory status in 1992 to regulate securities markets and protect investors.', 1),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q03', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The classification of a Money Bill is certified by the Speaker.
2. The Speaker''s decision on a Money Bill is final.
Which is/are correct?', '1 only', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', 'Both 1 and 2', 'D', 'The Speaker certifies a bill as a Money Bill under Article 110, and that decision is final.', 2),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q04', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'A Governor''s options on a bill under Article 200 include assent, withholding assent and:', 'Dissolving the assembly', 'Amending it directly', 'Reserving it for the President', 'Issuing an ordinance', 'C', 'Under Article 200 a Governor may assent, withhold assent, or reserve a bill for the President''s consideration.', 3),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q05', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Disinvestment of public sector undertakings is managed by which body?', 'DIPAM', 'RBI', 'SEBI', 'NITI Aayog', 'A', 'Disinvestment is managed by DIPAM (Department of Investment and Public Asset Management).', 4),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q06', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Consider the following statements:
1. The Election Commission conducts elections under Article 324.
2. The CAG audits and reports to Parliament under Article 148.
Which is/are correct?', 'Both 1 and 2', '2 only', 'Neither 1 nor 2', '1 only', 'A', 'The Election Commission acts under Article 324 and the CAG audits and reports under Article 148.', 5),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q07', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Inflation targeting in India is carried out by which body?', 'The Finance Commission', 'The Monetary Policy Committee of the RBI', 'The GST Council', 'SEBI', 'B', 'Inflation targeting is handled by the RBI''s Monetary Policy Committee (MPC).', 6),
  ('upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news-q08', 'upsc-current-affairs-polity-and-economy-in-the-news', 'Fiscal transfers between the Centre and the States are recommended by the:', 'GST Council', 'Finance Commission', 'NITI Aayog', 'RBI', 'B', 'The Finance Commission recommends fiscal transfers and tax devolution between the Centre and the States.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q01', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A body starts from rest and accelerates at 2 m/s². How far does it travel in 5 s?', '25 m', '20 m', '50 m', '10 m', 'A', 's = ut + ½at² = 0 + ½(2)(25) = 25 m.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q02', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A stone is dropped from rest. Its velocity after 3 s (g = 10 m/s²) is:', '30 m/s', '10 m/s', '20 m/s', '45 m/s', 'A', 'v = u + gt = 0 + 10 × 3 = 30 m/s.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q03', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'The area under a velocity–time graph represents:', 'Acceleration', 'Displacement', 'Jerk', 'Average speed', 'B', 'Integrating velocity over time gives displacement, which is the area under the v–t curve.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q04', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A car moving at 20 m/s decelerates uniformly and stops in 100 m. The deceleration is:', '1 m/s²', '10 m/s²', '2 m/s²', '4 m/s²', 'C', 'Using v² = u² + 2as: 0 = 400 + 2a(100), so a = −2 m/s².', 3),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q05', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'The distance covered in the n-th second by a body from rest with acceleration a is:', 'a(n − 1)', 'an', '½an²', '(a/2)(2n − 1)', 'D', 's_nth = u + (a/2)(2n − 1); with u = 0 it reduces to (a/2)(2n − 1).', 4),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q06', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'A ball thrown vertically up with 20 m/s reaches a maximum height of (g = 10 m/s²):', '30 m', '10 m', '20 m', '40 m', 'C', 'At the top v = 0, so h = u²/2g = 400/20 = 20 m.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q07', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'If velocity is negative and acceleration is positive, the body is:', 'Slowing down', 'Speeding up', 'At rest', 'Moving at constant speed', 'A', 'Opposite signs of v and a mean the speed (magnitude) is decreasing.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-kinematics-1d-q08', 'jee-physics-kinematics-1d', 'Two balls are dropped 1 s apart from the same height. As they fall, the gap between them:', 'Stays constant', 'Decreases', 'Increases', 'First increases then decreases', 'C', 'The earlier ball is always faster, so the separation grows with time.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q01', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The moment of inertia of a solid sphere about a diameter is:', 'MR²', '(2/5)MR²', '(1/2)MR²', '(2/3)MR²', 'B', 'A uniform solid sphere has I = (2/5)MR² about any diameter.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q02', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The rotational analogue of force is:', 'Momentum', 'Torque', 'Impulse', 'Power', 'B', 'Torque τ = Iα plays the role of force F = ma in rotation.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q03', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'A skater pulls in her arms while spinning. Her angular velocity:', 'Stays the same', 'Decreases', 'Increases', 'Becomes zero', 'C', 'With torque zero, L = Iω is conserved; reducing I increases ω.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q04', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'Which body reaches the bottom of an incline first while rolling without slipping?', 'Hollow cylinder', 'Hollow sphere', 'Ring', 'Solid sphere', 'D', 'The solid sphere has the smallest I/MR² (2/5), giving the largest acceleration.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q05', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The parallel axis theorem states I = :', 'I_cm − Md²', 'I_cm + Md²', 'I_cm + ½Md²', '2I_cm + Md²', 'B', 'I about a parallel axis equals the centre-of-mass value plus Md².', 4),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q06', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'For rolling without slipping, the velocity of the contact point with the ground is:', 'v', 'v/2', '2v', 'Zero', 'D', 'In pure rolling, the instantaneous velocity of the contact point is zero.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q07', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'The rotational kinetic energy of a body is:', '½Iω²', 'Iω²', '½Iω', '½I²ω', 'A', 'Rotational KE = ½Iω², analogous to ½mv² for translation.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-rotational-motion-q08', 'jee-physics-rotational-motion', 'A disc of moment of inertia 2 kg·m² spins at 3 rad/s. Its angular momentum is:', '3 kg·m²/s', '9 kg·m²/s', '5 kg·m²/s', '6 kg·m²/s', 'D', 'L = Iω = 2 × 3 = 6 kg·m²/s.', 7),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q01', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The shape of a molecule with sp³ hybridisation and no lone pairs is:', 'Tetrahedral', 'Trigonal planar', 'Linear', 'Octahedral', 'A', 'Four equivalent sp³ orbitals point to the corners of a tetrahedron (109.5°).', 0),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q02', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The bond angle in a water molecule is approximately:', '90°', '104.5°', '109.5°', '120°', 'B', 'Two lone pairs on the sp³ oxygen compress the H–O–H angle to about 104.5°.', 1),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q03', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'Which molecule has a zero net dipole moment despite polar bonds?', 'CO₂', 'NH₃', 'HCl', 'H₂O', 'A', 'CO₂ is linear and symmetric, so the two bond dipoles cancel exactly.', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q04', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The bond order of the oxygen molecule (O₂) from MO theory is:', '2', '1', '1.5', '3', 'A', 'O₂ has a bond order of 2 and two unpaired electrons, making it paramagnetic.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q05', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'According to Fajans'' rules, covalent character increases with:', 'Large cation, small anion', 'Small cation, large anion', 'Low cation charge', 'Large anion, large cation', 'B', 'A small, highly charged cation polarises a large anion, increasing covalent character.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q06', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The hybridisation of carbon in ethyne (C₂H₂) is:', 'sp', 'sp²', 'sp³', 'sp³d', 'A', 'The triple-bonded carbons in ethyne are sp hybridised, giving a linear molecule.', 5),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q07', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'The unusually high boiling point of water is mainly due to:', 'Ionic bonding', 'Hydrogen bonding', 'Van der Waals forces', 'Metallic bonding', 'B', 'Extensive hydrogen bonding between water molecules requires extra energy to break.', 6),
  ('jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding-q08', 'jee-chemistry-chemical-bonding', 'In the ammonium ion (NH₄⁺), the fourth N–H bond is a:', 'Ionic bond', 'Metallic bond', 'Hydrogen bond', 'Coordinate bond', 'D', 'The lone pair on nitrogen forms a coordinate (dative) bond with the proton.', 7),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q01', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'For the equation x² − 5x + 6 = 0, the sum of the roots is:', '6', '−5', '5', '−6', 'C', 'Sum of roots = −b/a = −(−5)/1 = 5 (roots are 2 and 3).', 0),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q02', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The discriminant of 2x² + 3x + 5 = 0 is:', '31', '−31', '49', '−49', 'B', 'D = b² − 4ac = 9 − 40 = −31, so the roots are complex.', 1),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q03', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'If the roots of a quadratic are equal, the discriminant is:', 'Zero', 'Negative', 'Irrational', 'Positive', 'A', 'Equal real roots occur exactly when D = b² − 4ac = 0.', 2),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q04', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The quadratic equation whose roots are 3 and −2 is:', 'x² − x − 6 = 0', 'x² + x − 6 = 0', 'x² − 5x + 6 = 0', 'x² + 5x + 6 = 0', 'A', 'Sum = 1, product = −6, so x² − (1)x + (−6) = x² − x − 6 = 0.', 3),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q05', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'For ax² + bx + c > 0 to hold for all real x, we require:', 'a > 0 and D > 0', 'a < 0 and D > 0', 'a < 0 and D < 0', 'a > 0 and D < 0', 'D', 'An upward parabola (a > 0) that never touches the x-axis (D < 0) is always positive.', 4),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q06', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'If α and β are roots of x² − 6x + 8 = 0, then α² + β² equals:', '16', '20', '36', '52', 'B', 'α² + β² = (α + β)² − 2αβ = 36 − 16 = 20.', 5),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q07', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The vertex of the parabola y = x² − 4x + 7 lies at x =:', '2', '1', '4', '−2', 'A', 'The vertex is at x = −b/(2a) = 4/2 = 2.', 6),
  ('jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations-q08', 'jee-mathematics-quadratic-equations', 'The product of the roots of 3x² − 12x + 9 = 0 is:', '1', '4', '3', '9', 'C', 'Product = c/a = 9/3 = 3.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q01', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A net force of 12 N acts on a 3 kg block. Its acceleration is:', '2 m/s²', '36 m/s²', '9 m/s²', '4 m/s²', 'D', 'By Newton''s second law a = F/m = 12/3 = 4 m/s².', 0),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q02', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Newton''s third law force pairs always act on:', 'The same body', 'Massless objects only', 'Two different bodies', 'The Earth only', 'C', 'Action and reaction are equal, opposite, and act on different bodies.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q03', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A block on a horizontal surface has mu_s = 0.5 and mass 4 kg (g = 10). Maximum static friction is:', '10 N', '40 N', '2 N', '20 N', 'D', 'f_max = mu_s x N = 0.5 x 4 x 10 = 20 N.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q04', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'The angle of repose theta for a surface with coefficient of friction mu satisfies:', 'sin(theta) = mu', 'cos(theta) = mu', 'tan(theta) = mu', 'theta = mu', 'C', 'A block just slides when tan(theta) equals the coefficient of static friction.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q05', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A person of mass 50 kg stands in a lift accelerating up at 2 m/s² (g = 10). Apparent weight is:', '500 N', '400 N', '600 N', '100 N', 'C', 'Apparent weight = m(g + a) = 50 x 12 = 600 N.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q06', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Impulse is equal to the change in:', 'Kinetic energy', 'Momentum', 'Acceleration', 'Power', 'B', 'Impulse J = F x t equals the change in momentum, by the impulse-momentum theorem.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q07', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'Two blocks of 2 kg and 3 kg connected by a string are pulled by 20 N on a frictionless floor. Acceleration is:', '10 m/s²', '6.7 m/s²', '4 m/s²', '2 m/s²', 'C', 'a = F/(m1 + m2) = 20/5 = 4 m/s².', 6),
  ('jee-physics-laws-of-motion-q08', 'jee-physics-laws-of-motion', 'A body in equilibrium under three forces means the forces:', 'Are all equal', 'Are perpendicular', 'Form a closed triangle', 'Have zero magnitude', 'C', 'Three concurrent forces in equilibrium add vectorially to zero, forming a closed triangle.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q01', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A force of 10 N moves a body 5 m in its own direction. Work done is:', '2 J', '15 J', '0 J', '50 J', 'D', 'W = F x s x cos(0) = 10 x 5 = 50 J.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q02', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'The kinetic energy of a 2 kg body moving at 3 m/s is:', '9 J', '6 J', '18 J', '3 J', 'A', 'KE = 0.5 x m x v² = 0.5 x 2 x 9 = 9 J.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q03', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'Work done by a force perpendicular to the displacement is:', 'Maximum', 'Equal to F x s', 'Zero', 'Negative', 'C', 'W = Fs cos(90) = 0; a perpendicular force does no work.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q04', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A spring of constant 200 N/m is stretched 0.1 m. Potential energy stored is:', '1 J', '2 J', '20 J', '10 J', 'A', 'PE = 0.5 x k x x² = 0.5 x 200 x 0.01 = 1 J.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q05', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'In a perfectly inelastic collision, the conserved quantity is:', 'Kinetic energy', 'Neither', 'Both KE and momentum', 'Momentum', 'D', 'Momentum is conserved in all collisions; kinetic energy is lost when inelastic.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q06', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'A 1000 W motor lifting a load does how much work in 10 s?', '100 J', '1000 J', '100000 J', '10000 J', 'D', 'W = P x t = 1000 x 10 = 10000 J.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q07', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'For a perfectly elastic collision, the coefficient of restitution e equals:', '0', '0.5', '2', '1', 'D', 'e = 1 for elastic collisions; e = 0 for perfectly inelastic ones.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-work-energy-power-q08', 'jee-physics-work-energy-power', 'The instantaneous power delivered by a force F to a body moving at velocity v is:', 'F/v', 'F + v', 'F x v', '0.5 F v²', 'C', 'Instantaneous power P equals the dot product F x v.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q01', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The escape velocity from Earth is approximately:', '11.2 km/s', '7.9 km/s', '3.0 km/s', '30 km/s', 'A', 'Earth''s escape velocity is about 11.2 km/s, equal to sqrt(2GM/R).', 0),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q02', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'If the distance between two masses is doubled, the gravitational force becomes:', 'Half', 'Four times', 'Double', 'One-quarter', 'D', 'Force varies as 1/r²; doubling r reduces it to one-quarter.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q03', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The value of g at a height equal to Earth''s radius R above the surface is:', 'g/4', 'g/2', 'g', 'g/9', 'A', 'At height R, distance from centre is 2R, so g'' = g/(2)² = g/4.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q04', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'Kepler''s third law states that the square of the orbital period is proportional to:', 'Orbital radius', 'Square of the radius', 'Cube of the radius', 'Mass of the planet', 'C', 'T² is proportional to r³, Kepler''s law of periods.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q05', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The orbital velocity of a satellite close to Earth''s surface relates to escape velocity by:', 'v_e = sqrt(2) v_o', 'v_e = 2 v_o', 'v_e = v_o', 'v_e = v_o/2', 'A', 'Escape velocity is sqrt(2) times the orbital velocity.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q06', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The period of a geostationary satellite is:', '24 hours', '12 hours', '1 hour', '365 days', 'A', 'A geostationary satellite matches Earth''s rotation with a 24-hour period.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q07', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'The gravitational potential energy of two masses separated by r is:', '-GMm/r', '+GMm/r', '-GMm/r²', 'GMm/r²', 'A', 'Gravitational PE is negative: U = -GMm/r, taken zero at infinity.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-gravitation-q08', 'jee-physics-gravitation', 'At the centre of the Earth, the acceleration due to gravity is:', 'Maximum', 'Equal to surface g', 'Infinite', 'Zero', 'D', 'g decreases linearly with depth and is zero at the centre.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q01', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'The time period of a simple pendulum of length L is:', '2*pi*sqrt(g/L)', '2*pi*sqrt(L/g)', '2*pi*sqrt(m/k)', 'sqrt(L/g)', 'B', 'The pendulum period is 2*pi*sqrt(L/g), independent of mass.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q02', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'In SHM, the acceleration is maximum at:', 'The mean position', 'The extreme position', 'Halfway', 'Everywhere equal', 'B', 'Acceleration a = -omega²x is maximum where displacement x is largest, at the extremes.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q03', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'A spring-mass system has k = 100 N/m and m = 1 kg. Its angular frequency is:', '5 rad/s', '10 rad/s', '100 rad/s', '1 rad/s', 'B', 'omega = sqrt(k/m) = sqrt(100) = 10 rad/s.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q04', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'Two tuning forks of 256 Hz and 260 Hz produce beats at a frequency of:', '2 Hz', '4 Hz', '8 Hz', '516 Hz', 'B', 'Beat frequency equals the difference, 260 - 256 = 4 Hz.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q05', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'The velocity of a wave with frequency 50 Hz and wavelength 4 m is:', '12.5 m/s', '200 m/s', '54 m/s', '100 m/s', 'B', 'v = f x lambda = 50 x 4 = 200 m/s.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q06', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'The total energy of a particle in SHM is proportional to:', 'Amplitude', 'Frequency only', 'Inverse of amplitude', 'Square of amplitude', 'D', 'Total energy E = 0.5 k A² is proportional to the square of the amplitude.', 5),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q07', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'The speed of a transverse wave on a stretched string depends on tension T and linear density mu as:', 'sqrt(T/mu)', 'sqrt(mu/T)', 'T x mu', 'T/mu', 'A', 'Wave speed on a string is v = sqrt(T/mu).', 6),
  ('jee-physics-shm-waves-q08', 'jee-physics-shm-waves', 'When a source of sound approaches a stationary observer, the observed frequency:', 'Decreases', 'Increases', 'Stays the same', 'Becomes zero', 'B', 'By the Doppler effect, an approaching source raises the observed pitch.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q01', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'The force between two charges is F. If each charge is doubled, the new force is:', '2F', '4F', 'F/2', 'F/4', 'B', 'F is proportional to the product of charges; doubling both gives 4F.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q02', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'The electric field inside a charged conductor in electrostatic equilibrium is:', 'Zero', 'Equal to the surface field', 'Maximum', 'Infinite', 'A', 'Charges reside on the surface, leaving the field inside a conductor zero.', 1),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q03', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'Electric potential is a:', 'Vector quantity', 'Always zero', 'Tensor', 'Scalar quantity', 'D', 'Potential is a scalar; potentials from multiple charges add algebraically.', 2),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q04', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'By Gauss''s law, the total electric flux through a closed surface depends on:', 'Surface area', 'Charge enclosed', 'Shape of the surface', 'External charges', 'B', 'Flux equals q_enclosed/epsilon0, independent of shape or external charges.', 3),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q05', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'Inserting a dielectric of constant K between capacitor plates changes capacitance to:', 'C/K', 'C unchanged', 'C + K', 'K x C', 'D', 'A dielectric raises capacitance by the factor K to K times C.', 4),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q06', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'The energy stored in a capacitor of capacitance C charged to voltage V is:', 'CV', '0.5 C V', 'C V²', '0.5 C V²', 'D', 'Stored energy is U = 0.5 x C x V².', 5),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q07', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'The electric field due to an infinite charged sheet of surface density sigma is:', 'sigma/(2 epsilon0)', 'sigma/epsilon0', 'Depends on distance', 'Zero', 'A', 'The field of an infinite sheet is sigma/(2 epsilon0), independent of distance.', 6),
  ('jee-physics-electrostatics-q08', 'jee-physics-electrostatics', 'The torque on an electric dipole of moment p in a field E at angle theta is:', 'pE', 'pE cos(theta)', 'pE sin(theta)', 'Zero always', 'C', 'Torque on a dipole is pE sin(theta), maximum when the dipole is perpendicular to the field.', 7),
  ('jee-physics-current-electricity-q01', 'jee-physics-current-electricity', 'A 12 V battery drives 3 A through a resistor. The resistance is:', '0.25 ohm', '36 ohm', '15 ohm', '4 ohm', 'D', 'By Ohm''s law R = V/I = 12/3 = 4 ohm.', 0),
  ('jee-physics-current-electricity-q02', 'jee-physics-current-electricity', 'Two resistors of 6 ohm each in parallel give an equivalent of:', '3 ohm', '6 ohm', '12 ohm', '1.5 ohm', 'A', 'Equal parallel resistors halve: 6/2 = 3 ohm.', 1),
