  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q01', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The maximum number of electrons in a shell with principal quantum number n is:', 'n', '2n', '2n²', 'n²', 'C', 'A shell holds at most 2n² electrons.', 0),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q02', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The principle that no two electrons can have all four quantum numbers identical is:', 'Aufbau principle', 'Hund''s rule', 'Heisenberg principle', 'Pauli exclusion principle', 'D', 'The Pauli exclusion principle forbids identical sets of four quantum numbers.', 1),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q03', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The azimuthal quantum number l for a d subshell is:', '0', '1', '3', '2', 'D', 'For d orbitals, l = 2 (s = 0, p = 1, d = 2, f = 3).', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q04', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The Balmer series of hydrogen corresponds to electron transitions ending at:', 'n = 1', 'n = 4', 'n = 3', 'n = 2', 'D', 'Balmer lines arise from transitions down to n = 2 and lie in the visible region.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q05', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'Hund''s rule of maximum multiplicity states that electrons:', 'Fill orbitals singly before pairing', 'Pair up first', 'Occupy the highest orbital', 'Always pair with opposite spin', 'A', 'Degenerate orbitals are singly filled before any pairing occurs.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q06', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The electronic configuration of chromium (Z = 24) is anomalous as:', '[Ar] 3d4 4s2', '[Ar] 3d5 4s1', '[Ar] 3d6 4s0', '[Ar] 3d3 4s3', 'B', 'Chromium adopts 3d5 4s1 for the extra stability of a half-filled d subshell.', 5),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q07', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'Heisenberg''s uncertainty principle relates the uncertainties in:', 'Position and momentum', 'Charge and mass', 'Energy and charge', 'Spin and mass', 'A', 'It states delta x times delta p is at least h/(4 pi).', 6),
