  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q01', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'In RC, a factual question is best answered by:', 'Guessing', 'Prior knowledge', 'Locating the exact line in the passage', 'Choosing the longest option', 'C', 'Factual answers are found by locating the exact line in the passage.', 0),
  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q02', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'An inference answer should:', 'Go far beyond the text', 'Stay one safe step beyond the text', 'Contradict the text', 'Ignore the text', 'B', 'A good inference stays one safe step beyond the passage.', 1),
  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q03', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'Answers in reading comprehension should be based on:', 'The passage only', 'General knowledge', 'Personal opinion', 'Other passages', 'A', 'RC answers must come strictly from the passage, not prior knowledge.', 2),
  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q04', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'Which word describes a neutral author tone?', 'Objective', 'Sceptical', 'Critical', 'Appreciative', 'A', 'Objective and descriptive indicate a neutral tone.', 3),
  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q05', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'A common RC trap is choosing an option that is:', 'True in real life but unsupported by the passage', 'Supported by the passage', 'Directly quoted', 'The main idea', 'A', 'A trap is an option true in real life but not supported by the passage.', 4),
  ('ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension-q06', 'ssc-cgl-english-reading-comprehension', 'For vocabulary-in-context questions, the best method is to:', 'Use the dictionary meaning only', 'Pick the hardest word', 'Replace the word with each option and test the fit', 'Skip the question', 'C', 'Replace the word with each option and test the fit in context.', 5),
