  ('gate-core-cs-compiler-design-q06', 'gate-core-cs-compiler-design', 'Three-address code is an example of:', 'Intermediate code', 'Source code', 'Target machine code', 'A token', 'A', 'Three-address code is a common intermediate representation.', 5),
  ('gate-core-cs-compiler-design-q07', 'gate-core-cs-compiler-design', 'Compared with LL parsers, LR parsers generally handle:', 'A smaller class of grammars', 'Only regular grammars', 'No grammars at all', 'A larger class of grammars', 'D', 'Bottom-up LR parsers accept a broader class of grammars than LL parsers.', 6),
  ('gate-core-cs-compiler-design-q08', 'gate-core-cs-compiler-design', 'Syntax-directed translation attaches semantic rules to:', 'Tokens', 'Grammar productions', 'Registers', 'Machine instructions', 'B', 'Syntax-directed translation associates semantic actions with grammar productions.', 7),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q01', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'Which memory is the fastest in the typical hierarchy?', 'Registers', 'Main memory', 'Hard disk', 'Cache', 'A', 'Registers sit closest to the CPU and are the fastest storage.', 0),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q02', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'An ideal k-stage instruction pipeline offers a maximum speedup of about:', '2 times', 'log k times', 'k squared times', 'k times', 'D', 'An ideal k-stage pipeline can approach a k-fold speedup.', 1),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q03', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'In direct-mapped cache, a memory block maps to:', 'Any cache line', 'Exactly one fixed cache line', 'Any line within one set', 'Two specific lines', 'B', 'Direct mapping sends each block to one predetermined cache line.', 2),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q04', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'Which is a type of pipeline hazard?', 'Cache hazard', 'Data hazard', 'Register hazard', 'Address hazard', 'B', 'Data, control, and structural hazards are the three pipeline hazard types.', 3),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q05', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'If the cache hit ratio is 0.9 with cache time 10 ns and memory time 100 ns, average access time is:', '19 ns', '10 ns', '100 ns', '90 ns', 'A', 'Average is 0.9 times 10 plus 0.1 times 100, equal 9 plus 10, which is 19 ns.', 4),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q06', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'The metric CPI stands for:', 'Cache per instruction', 'Cycles per instruction', 'Calls per interrupt', 'Clocks per input', 'B', 'CPI is cycles per instruction, a key performance measure.', 5),
  ('gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture-q07', 'gate-core-cs-computer-organization-architecture', 'Which is the correct order of basic instruction-cycle steps?', 'Execute, fetch, decode, write-back', 'Write-back, execute, decode, fetch', 'Decode, fetch, write-back, execute', 'Fetch, decode, execute, write-back', 'D', 'The cycle proceeds fetch, decode, execute, then write-back.', 6),
